-- Home Depot's Fernandez to resign as general counsel
-- 
-- Thu Feb 1, 2007 4:52pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/01/businesspro-homedepot-execs-dc-idUSWEN344420070201

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - Home Depot Inc. ( HD.N ) said on 
Thursday that Frank Fernandez would step down as general 
counsel and Dennis Donovan will leave as executive vice 
president of human resources, effective February 14. 


  Home Depot promoted Tim Crow, senior vice president for 
talent, organization and performance systems, to executive vice 
president of human resources. Jim Snyder, vice president of 
litigation and risk management, will serve as interim head of 
the company's legal department.